The paper discusses multiple access techniques for machine-to-machine (M2M) communications in future wireless cellular networks. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and the sub-category of network architecture and design (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the throughput efficiency of different multiple access techniques, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The use of multiple access techniques for M2M communications also involves system-level considerations, such as coordination and synchronization, which fall under the category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the emerging Internet of Things (IoT), which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.CR).
